description.narrative: Despite the heavy shelling that targeted health facilities in North West Syria (NWS), UNICEF has continued delivering essential health services in strategic areas to ensure equity and access. UNICEF supported essential primary and secondary health services for 227,931 people, 2 polio vaccination campaign that reached 867,952 children under 5 as well as a routine EPI programme that delivered DPT3 vaccine for 108,899 children under 1. A total of 922,660 caregivers and guardians received health promotion messages to improve the health status of their children and 29 professionals were trained on Neonatal Resuscitation techniques | Status:On-track | As-of Date:09/04/2020
